widgets_values:
With WilcardMode enable
1-. Enter the text prompt using the categoy name __Category__ to indicate the field that should be replace by values from the wildcards.yaml or .json file
2. Use __Category/*__ to select rendom value from the item list use __Category/**__ to select the random value from within the subdirectories
3. Enter the dynamic_prompt select the variable name for the category then enter the equal simbol= and the values between curly brackets{} values separated by pipes| Color={red|blue|white|black} the script will create a prompt for each values overriding the values contained on the wildcards yaml or json file for the specific categories variables
4. select the maximun variant prompts you need with max_variants counter connect the text_list to a display text node
5. Execute the node

A surreal lunar landscape where a spaceship marked XXI-1883 lies crashed amidst alien flora. An astronaut in dynamic pose, examining wreckage, bathed in starlight. Fantastical moon with exaggerated texture looming large in the sky. A fairy-like creature with butterfly wings hovers curiously near. Distant futuristic craft flies through space, adding depth to the dreamlike sci-fi scene.

select folder make sure to copy the address from the search bar and paste it into the pop up or directly into the input path hit refresh select your range of images to work with if the images are too large the api won't recognise it so you either resize them manualy or use the resizer node before feeding them to PromptImaGEN
If the images aren't too important you can use the backup button on the node otherwise I recommend saving your work before you start using this.

This Node works with various local and api Models providers to generate prompts. 
##Profiles
Some Profiles are too complex for weaker models but you can easily edit the profiles they are system prompts to control the models behaviour
some of then contain reflection and evaluation rules so those are going to be more for powerful models.

##Auto
The Normal model and Omost strategies can be loop when Auto is enable over the total of images you fed with IFLoadImagesS. 
Firts you need to set the settings for the loop run you need to make sure to select the llm settings and store them before running the queue you need to set one of the The IF_Auto profiles which will attempt to create a prompt for the images automatically. Is better to leave the other presets as None.
After storing the settings you can select the actual settings for the strategy the provider can be different

The settings 
The Ai_fill attempts to generate a negative base on the generated positive prompt and the original image.
The Combo mode loops the images one by one while the Mix takes batches of 4 images at once which is great for making prompts base on elemts from a group of images.

##Omost   
For Omost mode you need to install the DenseDiffusion node and Omost nodes. I provide a model via Ollama but for the conditioning nodes get the extra extensions
https://github.com/huchenlei/ComfyUI_densediffusion
https://github.com/huchenlei/ComfyUI_omost
https://ollama.com/impactframes/dolphin_llama3_omost:latest

##Create
Create mode just uses OpenAI APIs to generate images but I will add other ways Next 
The edit and variation have not been tested yet
